(4/4) Feel free to share Ukrainian art and artists in my thread â¤ï¸

(3/4) I think about that story often. And I think that art matters. Keep sharing your story. Keep sharing beauty. In the time of war, you will be amazed how beauty can lift the spirit to keep going. Sending all love and strength to everyone in Ukraine ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¦

(2/4) I'm from Vietnam and have heard many stories about how devastating war is from my parents. One story I remember vividly was about my grandfather. During the Vietnam War, he started a pocket poem movement. People passed patriotic poems to lift up the spirit of the soldiers.

(1/4) I have seen Ukraine artists trying to sell their art over the past couple days. I want artists to know that what you are doing is important â¤ï¸ The world is watching you. Your stories and your art matter. When resources are scarce, beauty matter more than ever.
